Advantages of Using a Proxy (Vite 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Gunicorn)\
1. No CORS problems in development\
Without a proxy:\
Frontend runs at: http://localhost:5173\
Backend runs at: http://127.0.0.1:8000\
These are different origins, so every API call (like /api/reservations) triggers CORS checks.\
Symptoms:\
CORS error in the browser\
Need to configure allowed origins\
Need to restart backend every .env change\
With a proxy:\
Requests from React appear to come from localhost:5173\
Vite forwards /api/... internally to Gunicorn\
Browser never sees the cross-origin hop\
No CORS configuration, no CORS errors.\
This alone is usually enough reason to use a proxy.\
